An #RStats nested-loop feature I abuse in this #wordle-engine-in-a-tweet - the same variable looped over in the inner and outer loops have different scopes

I.e. 'i' is always 1:5, but 'j' loops over an ever-decreasing vector - even though they refer to same variable https://t.co/jwkAMK7KWR

#RStats #wordle in a tweet
s=\(x)el(strsplit(x,''))
t=s(sample(grep("^[a-z]{5}$",readLines('/usr/share/dict/words'),v=T),1))
while(1){g=s(readline("? "))
M=t==g
r=which(!M)
